post_text:
Based on the guidance from the Arizona Department of Education, we are planning to reopen our school on August 4, 2020. We will plan to open with increased safety precautions such as daily health screening protocols, physical distancing where possible, and more frequent and improved cleaning and sanitation processes. In additions, we will encourage students and employees to wear masks; however, we respect that is a personal choice and face masks will not be required.

We also plan to offer remote learning for families who do not feel comfortable returning to school in person yet.

We are excited to be able to see your children and provide them with the best learning experience possible. Please contact ACP to be certain your enrollment form for your student is updated.

We also encourage you to please contact us with any questions or concerns your may have.

We look forward to a healthy, successful 2020-2021 school year!

* How to prepare for and prevent COVID-19 spread,
* Testing information for COVID-19,
* What populations are at higher risk from the COVID-19,
* What to do if an individual gets sick,
* COVID-19 and animals,
* And a list of websites with accurate, reliable and up-to-date information.
The line will operate from 8:00 a.m. to 8:00 p.m. each day of the week and can be reached by dialing 2-1-1 while an individual is located in Arizona.

post_text:
To our parents and to the Mesa and east-valley community: It‚Äôs nearing the end of the year and our school can use your financial donations. Remember, besides being a Title I school, we are also a 501(c)(3) charity under the federal IRS code.

The Arizona State Tax Credit program allows you to make a donation to an eligible organization (that‚Äôs us...) and receive a dollar-for-dollar credit against Arizona state taxes owed. Up to $400 for married couples; $200 for those over 18 years old and single.

We have our first-ever Baseball team this coming season. Plus, ACP may endeavor in other sports as well. Our students deserve a great sports program. Don‚Äôt you think?

So please donate what you can, $50, $100, or even the full $400 ($200 for those single and over 18 years old.)

The teachers and staff thank you in advance. Go Lions...!

It's been almost a week since school has started, and its likely students at Mountain View High School or Mesa High School have received their first homework assignments. But don't be sad... ACP High School gives no homework, and luckily, we still have open enrollment.

And, we have experienced and certified teachers just like the big schools. So if you want your weekends free from doing homework, just stop by our campus located west of Gilbert Rd. and north of University Dr. Awesome huh?

Oh, I forgot to tell you we only have 4-day school weeks with no-school on Friday's. Wow..! Also, we are expanding our sports program to include girls and boys volleyball, girls and boys basketball, flag football, possibly co-ed soccer or baseball, and girls and boys beach volleyball.

post_text:
If you are looking for a small school with seasoned and fully-certified teachers, why would you look anywhere else?

We are located near University & Gilbert Road. Please come to our campus and see what we have to offer.

At our school, we educate students in inventive ways. Also, you really will love our FOUR-DAY school week!! üòâ Yes, that's right, four-day week, which means no school on fridays!!

We have some new changes this year, including our new 'independent study' program. One requirement is to meet with your teachers once a week for about an hour. There are other small rules and qualifications for this, so please speak with one of our administrators.
